history.content:
On behalf of the Spring 2018 CS 189 staff, I invite you to apply for our Academic Intern role.

Becoming an Academic Intern is a great way to reinforce what you've learned, help students (as you were helped), become a better teacher, and keep in touch with the community. Furthermore, academic interning is one of the first steps you can take if you're interested in reading or TA’ing in the future. This past semester, academic interns were responsible for hosting CS 189 Guerrilla Sections and running office hours, allowing them to develop skills highly desired in a CS 189 TA - logistics experience, a passion for the material, and a desire to go above and beyond.

Please note that academic interning requires you to be responsible and hard-working, which is why we require you to enroll in either 1 or 2 pass/no pass units. While we do not impose a minimum grade cutoff, please note that we are expecting a high number of applicants.

The deadline for the application is Monday January 22nd. You may find it here.
history.subject: CS 189 Academic Intern Application
